text: Govt. Gurudayal College or Gurudayal College () is a public college under National University located in Kishoreganj Municipality, Kishoreganj Sadar Upazila, Kishoreganj, Bangladesh. The college was established in 1943. == Notable alumni == * Abdul Hamid, 16th president of Bangladesh. * Amir Hossain, justice of the Supreme Court of Bangladesh. ==References== Category:Educational institutions established in 1943 Category:Universities and colleges in Bangladesh Category:1943 establishments in India Category:Colleges in Kishoreganj District
title: Gurudayal Government College
